217
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:38,240
You are not a fish, so how can you know a fish's happiness?

218
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:42,200
Now, the Second Young Master is also living

219
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:43,879
the life he wanted.

220
00:13:44,639 --> 00:13:48,879
Those who are alive aren't necessarily freer than the dead.

221
00:13:49,159 --> 00:13:54,080
The clear-minded aren't necessarily more at ease than the mad.

222
00:13:55,759 --> 00:13:56,799
You really do see things clearly.

223
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,519
I've always been a flawed person.

224
00:13:59,799 --> 00:14:02,120
I've come to terms with some things long ago.

225
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,679
Heaven and earth were never perfect to begin with.

226
00:14:05,039 --> 00:14:06,639
How could people be any different?

227
00:14:09,360 --> 00:14:11,159
I used to underestimate you.

228
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,600
It's not too late to think highly of you now.

229
00:14:22,919 --> 00:14:25,320
Congratulations, Master.

230
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:54,159
Fishing on dry land

231
00:15:55,039 --> 00:15:56,320
